# Release Notes

@summary
A real docs page with prose, structured sections, tables, code, and local references.

Lessmark uses plain prose for paragraphs and typed blocks when structure matters.

@toc

## Highlights

@list kind="unordered"
- Parser, formatter, and validator stay in sync.
- The site renders code, math, diagrams, tables, and callouts.
- Public packages share the same fixture set.

@decision id="canonical-format"
Formatting is part of the language contract, not a cosmetic option.

@reference target="canonical-format" label="canonical format"

@table columns="Surface|Status|Notes"
JavaScript|done|Parser and renderer
Python|done|Parser and CLI
Rust|done|Parser and CLI

## Example

@code lang="lessmark"
# Notes

Plain prose.

@task status="todo"
Write the next section.

@math notation="tex"
E = mc^2

@diagram kind="mermaid"
graph TD
  A --> B

@callout kind="tip" title="Stable output"
Run {{code:lessmark format file.lmk}} before committing generated docs.

@footnote id="fixtures"
Fixtures are parsed by every package in conformance tests.
